    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Previous names",
            "shortText": "<p><i>Dorotheanthus bellidiformis, Mesembryanthemum bellidiformis</i></p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_9_9969",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Low-growing tufted annual with tongue or paddle-shaped leaves that are covered in glistening bladder cells. The exquisite flowers are solitary and borne on naked stalks about 40 mm long. The flowers open only in sunlight and are flat with numerous, long, pink, orange or yellow petals. There is usually a paler halo towards the base and a darker center.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_9970",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Plant typically about 10 cm across, flowers 20-30 mm in diameter.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_9971",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to South Africa, but widely marketed worldwide as an ornamental garden plant.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Namaqualand to Southern Cape.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_9972",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Short-lived species adapted to disturbed areas and found both along the coast and inland, usually on sandy substrata. Forms spectacular displays along the west coast in spring where is a favourite for photographers.</p><p>A popular garden plant that has been distributed around the world and is available in many colours.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_9973",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_9974",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Flowers July to October. Fruit a five-compartment capsule that expands in wet weather to reveal tiny, smooth, light-brown seeds. Seeds germinate with the first autumn rains and reach maturity by the spring.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_9975",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>A distinctive species but vary variable in flower colour so has a complicated taxonomic history and many synonyms.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_9976",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        }
    ],
